# Tests
## App

### Context menu listeners
When a context menu listener is created in a feature, it should be registered in background service.
- The text in context menu should be the feature name.

### Shortcuts listeners
When a shortcut listener is created in a feature, it should be registered in background service.

### Tab events listeners
When a tab create event listener is created in a feature, it should be registered in background service.
When a tab update event listener is created in a feature, it should be registered in background service.
When a tab remove event listener is created in a feature, it should be registered in background service.

When a tab is created it should execute the tab create event listeners.
When a tab is updated it should execute the tab update event listeners.
When a tab is removed it should execute the tab remove event listeners.

